@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Policies & Guidelines";
}

<div class="container mt-5 mb-5">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-10 offset-lg-1">
            <div class="card shadow border-0">
                <div class="card-body p-5">
                    <h1 class="mb-4 text-center text-primary fw-bold">Channel Partner Policies & Terms of Use</h1>
                    <p class="lead text-muted text-center mb-5">These policies govern your use of the CPRM platform. By continuing to use this platform, you agree to comply with these guidelines in full.</p>

                    <section class="mb-5">
                        <h3 class="text-secondary">1. Introduction</h3>
                        <p>
                            Welcome to the CPRM system, developed and managed by Pindah Private Limited. This platform has been designed to support and empower agents and partners in distributing telecom products such as SIM cards, routers, recharge vouchers, and related services. These policies aim to ensure fairness, security, and operational efficiency throughout our ecosystem.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section class="mb-5">
                        <h3 class="text-secondary">2. Account Registration and Verification</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>All users must submit valid identification (ID document and live photo) during registration.</li>
                            <li>Incomplete or falsified information will result in account rejection or deactivation without notice.</li>
                            <li>Account access is contingent on verification and approval by the administrative team.</li>
                            <li>Each user must maintain only one active account unless explicitly authorized.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="mb-5">
                        <h3 class="text-secondary">3. User Roles and Responsibilities</h3>
                        <p>
                            The system recognizes distinct user roles, including <strong>Agent</strong> and <strong>Administrator</strong>. Each role carries unique privileges and responsibilities. Role assignment is handled centrally and users are expected to operate within their defined scope.
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Agents are expected to represent the organization professionally and ethically.</li>
                            <li>Administrators hold the right to audit, manage, and modify system-level data.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="mb-5">
                        <h3 class="text-secondary">4. Product Usage and Handling</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>All products listed in the CPRM catalog are subject to stock availability and may change at any time without prior notice.</li>
                            <li>Agents are responsible for securely handling and accurately distributing products such as recharge vouchers, SIMs, routers, etc.</li>
                            <li>Products must not be tampered with, resold illegally, or exported beyond allowed boundaries.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="mb-5">
                        <h3 class="text-secondary">5. Pricing and Payments</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Pricing for each product is clearly listed on the platform and may be revised periodically.</li>
                            <li>Payments must be completed through approved gateways – currently, <strong>EcoCash</strong> is the only supported method.</li>
                            <li>Failed payments will automatically cancel associated orders. System-generated receipts will be provided upon success.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="mb-5">
                        <h3 class="text-secondary">6. Security and System Integrity</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Users must keep credentials confidential. Sharing passwords is a breach of policy.</li>
                            <li>Unauthorized access attempts will be logged and reported.</li>
                            <li>Deliberate misuse of the platform—including excessive traffic, spam actions, or abuse—will lead to permanent bans.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="mb-5">
                        <h3 class="text-secondary">7. Training and Documentation</h3>
                        <p>
                            The CPRM platform offers agents access to manuals, training videos, guides, and FAQs. These materials are proprietary and may not be redistributed or modified.
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Training is required before agents can begin full operations.</li>
                            <li>All documents must be read thoroughly. Acknowledge the agreement checkbox before using the system fully.</li>
                            <li>Any questions may be directed to the support chatbot or a supervisor.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="mb-5">
                        <h3 class="text-secondary">8. Communication and Chatbot Use</h3>
                        <p>
                            The integrated chatbot is available 24/7 to assist agents with queries related to operations, product availability, or system features.
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Use polite and concise language when interacting with the chatbot or any support system.</li>
                            <li>Do not attempt to exploit or reverse-engineer the chatbot's functionality.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="mb-5">
                        <h3 class="text-secondary">9. Legal and Regulatory Compliance</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>All users must comply with Zimbabwe’s laws and telecom regulatory requirements.</li>
                            <li>Breaches may be reported to national authorities, especially in cases involving fraud or theft.</li>
                            <li>We reserve the right to cooperate with law enforcement and share relevant data if required by law.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="mb-5">
                        <h3 class="text-secondary">10. Termination of Access</h3>
                        <p>
                            Your access to the CPRM system may be terminated at any time if:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>You violate any of the above policies.</li>
                            <li>You attempt to defraud, mislead, or damage the organization’s reputation.</li>
                            <li>Your account is inactive for more than 180 days without justification.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="mb-5">
                        <h3 class="text-secondary">11. Amendments and Policy Revisions</h3>
                        <p>
                            These policies may be updated periodically. Users will be notified of significant changes, but it remains your responsibility to review the policy page regularly.
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Use of the platform after any change constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.</li>
                            <li>All historical versions of this document can be requested in writing.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section class="text-center mt-5">
                        <p class="text-muted fst-italic">Issued by HIT400 | Last Updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</p>
                        <p class="text-muted">For any clarifications, contact <a href="mailto:admin@test.org">admin@test.org</a>.</p>
                    </section>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
